title: Ren Skincare font – rounded sans serif
content:
Anyone know what this is or anything similar?

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20150325212542im_/http:/typophile.com/files/ren_3691.jpg)
author: Arran

comments.content: Just to be precise: This it <cite>not</cite> [Houschka Rounded](http://web.archive.org/), as a detailed comparison reveals — at least not the retail version. However, only some letters differ noticeably. Anyone who cannot superimpose the glyphs will have a hard time telling Houschka apart from typeface used in the logo.

You're right R.

I saw this a few weeks ago and even I thought it was Houschka Rounded at first, until closer inspection revealed it wasn't. The K is the most immediate difference, and my R has a deeper bowl.

I too would like to know what it is.
